name: Belt_SetDict
docstrings: This module separates identity from data. It is a bit more verbose but slightly more efficient due to the fact that there is no need to pack identity and data back after each operation.

items.name: t
docstrings:
`'value` is the element type

  `'identity` the identity of the collection

docstrings: Type of compare function.


minimum
docstrings:
Returns minimum value of the collection. `None` if collection is empty.

  ```res example
  module IntCmp = Belt.Id.MakeComparable({
    type t = int
    let cmp = Pervasives.compare
  })

  let s0 = Belt.Set.Dict.empty
  let s1 = Belt.Set.Dict.fromArray([3, 2, 1, 5], ~cmp=IntCmp.cmp)

  s0->Belt.Set.Dict.minimum /* None */
  s1->Belt.Set.Dict.minimum /* Some(1) */
  ```
